<topic id="preferences-editor-pages">
  <title>Edit modes Preferences</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Configure the Application<indexterm>Editor
              preferences<indexterm>pages</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The <uicontrol>Edit modes</uicontrol> preferences page allows you to select the initial edit
      mode of an editor. The previous editing mode is saved and used at start-up. To configure the
        <uicontrol>Edit modes</uicontrol> options, <ph
        conkeyref="reusable.menus/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Edit modes</uicontrol>
      </menucascade> .</p>
    <p product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse">If the checkbox <uicontrol>Allow Document
        Type specific edit mode setting to override the general mode setting</uicontrol> is enabled,
      the initial edit mode setting set in <xref href="dg-author-settings.dita#dg-author-settings"
        format="dita">the Document Type dialog</xref> overrides the general edit mode setting from
      the table below.</p>
    <p>The initial edit mode of each editor type has one of the following values:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Text;</li>
      <li product="author authorEclipse editor editorEclipse">Author;</li>
      <li>Grid;</li>
      <li>Design (available only for the W3C XML Schema editor).</li>
    </ul>
